Freddie website theme + YAML caveats (2026-05-03): (1) Structured-YAML rendering — website/theme.mjs (164L) renders structured YAML via 247420 design vocabulary, not raw markdown. Consumes page.hero (heading/subheading/accent/body/badges/ctas), page.sections[] (rotating rail color green→purple→mascot→sun→flame→sky by section index, optional lede + per-item benefit italic), page.examples[] (railed link list with mono numeric ranks + ↗ glyph). Falls back to page.body markdown. Style block inlined so rail/dot/chip/btn classes work without ds-247420 SDK CSS. To get specific rail color, reorder sections. (2) YAML colon-space trap — in website/content/pages/*.yaml, any value containing ": " outside backticks (e.g. [linux, macos, windows], requiresEnv: ['MY_KEY']) MUST be double-quoted. Parser otherwise interprets embedded colon as mapping. Hit twice: tools.yaml line 72, skills.yaml line 40. (3) SSR innerHTML injection beats client dispatch — anentrypoint-design exposes Hero/HomeView/Panel/Row/Section/WorksList, but pre-mounted SSR injection via innerHTML more reliable than dispatching client-side at build — avoids depending on SDK loading before static HTML paints.